2.4.2 Iterating over numbers: ranges and progressions
	- Kotlin uses the conecpts of ranges.

	- use ".." operator for range
		ex) 
			======================================================
			val oneToTen = 1..10 // inclusive
			======================================================

	- "progression" 
		-> if you can iterate over all the values in a range, it is called progression



	- you can set "step"
		ex)
			======================================================
			for(i in 100 downTo 1 step 2){
				println(i)
			}
			======================================================

	- iterate over half-closed ranges, which don't include the specified point. (..<)
		ex)
			======================================================
			for(x in 0..<10)
				println(x)
			======================================================
